# Applications — folder structure

Every project under `applications/` uses this layout. Shared application rules live only in root `.cursor/rules/`. Do not keep parallel copies under `applications/rules/`, `applications/.cursor/`, or `applications/{project}/.cursor/`.

## Required layout per project

`applications/{project}/`

1. **Project root** — **project-specific** build script(s) only (e.g. `build_{project}_docs.py`). Each project owns its own generator: unique content, section order, and layout choices for that call. Do **not** use a shared/generic application generator, shared SPECS module, or one script that stamps many projects. Do **not** keep `tools/application_docs/` or similar cross-project doc factories.
2. **`documents/`** — exactly three synced deliverables:
   - `{project}_pdf.pdf`
   - `{project}_ppt.pptx`
   - `{project}_word.docx`
   No drafts, duplicates, or legacy copies. PowerPoint must meet the elegant deck standard in `.cursor/rules/documents.mdc` (balance, pictures, visual design, purposeful motion).
3. **`rules/`** — call-specific rules only (typically `source_of_truth.mdc`). One copy; never mirror under `.cursor/`. Scope each SoT with globs (`alwaysApply: false`). Point deck quality back to `documents.mdc` rather than duplicating long PPT rules here.

## Opportunities (outside applications/)

`opportunities/` keeps its tracker (`opportunities.xlsx`), build script, and `rules/source_of_truth.mdc`. Same rule: one SoT copy; no second tree under `opportunities/.cursor/`. Scope with `globs: opportunities/**`.

## Shared rules (root `.cursor/rules/`)

These are the only shared rules. Do not copy them under `applications/` or `opportunities/`.

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `folder_structure.mdc` | This layout |
| `documents.mdc` | Sync + elegant PowerPoint / cover standards |
| `instructions.mdc` | Writing style, .mdc word limit, deck quality pointer |
| `fairbanks-community-reach.mdc` | Operating model / cascade |
| `fairbanks_raw_project_idea.mdc` | Original FCHIP vision (do not edit) |
| `fairBanks_refined_project_idea.mdc` | Refined FairBanks narrative; FCHIP as FairBanks component |

## Assets & temp

- Media may come from repo `assets/` or a project `assets/` subfolder — prefer real photos, diagrams, maps, and dashboards in decks.
- Final edited docs live only in `documents/`.
- Temporary and build artifacts go in repo `tmp/` (gitignored).

## Example

```
.cursor/rules/
  folder_structure.mdc
  documents.mdc
  instructions.mdc
  fairbanks-community-reach.mdc
  fairbanks_raw_project_idea.mdc
  fairBanks_refined_project_idea.mdc
applications/
  {project}/
    build_{project}_docs.py
    rules/
      source_of_truth.mdc
    documents/
      {project}_pdf.pdf
      {project}_ppt.pptx
      {project}_word.docx
opportunities/
  build_opportunities.py
  opportunities.xlsx
  rules/
    source_of_truth.mdc
```

Apply this to every `applications/` project. No duplicate deliverables and no duplicate rule trees for the same content.
